The paper deals with anomaly detection, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The use of similarity-based algorithms and the definition of multiple dissimilarity measures suggest that the paper belongs to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of Pareto optimality and multicriteria analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Decision Making (cs.DM). The experiments with synthetic and real data sets suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Statistical Learning (cs.SI) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), depending on the nature of the data sets used. Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.SI, and cs.CR.
